div.p:
Against these Ambi-dexter Christians, (so to call them) who drawe their Soules perdition in the ropes of a supine and careles security, I haue thought good to vndergoe the wryting of this short ensuing Treatise, styling it; One God, one Fayth, according to the words of the
         Ephes. 4. Apostle;

 implying hereby, That, as there is but one God, and not many; so this one God wilbe truly worshipped (for the sauing of our Soules) with one, only, entyre, and perfect Fayth, and not with multiplicity of Religions.
